### Why the `values.update.yml` `sed` isn't saving you either

Even when `update-tag` runs correctly, look at the `helm:deploy` command:

```bash
helm upgrade --install ${RELEASE_NAME} \
  ${ENV}/charts/${SERVICE_NAME} \
  -n ${NAMESPACE} \
  -f ${ENV}/charts/${SERVICE_NAME}/values.yaml \
  --set image.tag=${VERSION} \      ← VERSION is empty here too
  --history-max=${HELM_HISTORY_MAX}
```

`--set image.tag=` (empty) overrides whatever `values.update.yml` wrote to `values.yaml`. So even if the sed update ran perfectly, the `--set` with empty VERSION wins. Both problems must be fixed together.
